            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ed Tanous",
                        "email": "ed@tanous.net",
                        "username": "edtanous"
                    },
                    "message": "I haven't read the content of this yet, but there are close to 6 different design docs out for various \"device specific firmware update\" things in review.\n\nPlease work together to converge on one document that meets everyone needs.  This means that everyone needs to cross review everyone elses design doc and come to a conclusion on what the superset of what we need is, who is going to execute on what portions, and how we're going to make it interop across the various things that need it."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kumar Thangavel",
                        "email": "thangavel.k@hcl.com",
                        "username": "HCL-BMC"
                    },
                    "message": "Ack. I will check on Device specific firmware update patches."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kumar Thangavel",
                        "email": "thangavel.k@hcl.com",
                        "username": "HCL-BMC"
                    },
                    "message": "https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-bmc-code-mgmt/blob/master/obmc-flash-host-bios%40.service.in\n\nAs per the service file in phosphor-bmc-code-mgmt, the custom flash tool will be called for flashing process. \n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/37950/16/designs/software-update-for-multiple-devices.md#191\n\nAs per the proposal to support multiple devices update, the custom flash tool will be called in service for flashing process. \n\nCustom flash tool is platform specific and with OEM and IPMB based. Current software update daemon follows this custom tool logic only. This design doc specifies only this custom tool design and implementation and not specific to firmware update.\n\nphosphor-ipmi-flash - This is different, It uses the BLOB protocol to transfer the firmware image. It follows the commands based on BlockTransfer. But Ours is more specific to IPMI OEM commands which has OEM based netfn and cmds for requesting firmware update and image transferring. So, we cannot use phosphor-ipmi-flash."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ed Tanous",
                        "email": "ed@tanous.net",
                        "username": "edtanous"
                    },
                    "message": "None of the above are design docs.  Please look at, and contribute to a single design doc (the requirements section at this point) that meets everyones needs."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kumar Thangavel",
                        "email": "thangavel.k@hcl.com",
                        "username": "HCL-BMC"
                    },
                    "message": "https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/50509\n\nThis design doc explains about Firmware updates and telemetry for i2c devices only. This design proposed to move the phosphor-bmc-code-mgnt/Itemupdater code and functionalities to the dbus-sensors to avoid the synchronisation and run time issues while doing firmware updating and polling sensors values. \n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/52234\n\nThis design doc explains about PMBus based devices (PSUSensor) only. This design proposed to move the phosphor-bmc-code-mgnt/Itemupdater code and functionalities to the dbus-sensors(PSUSensor) to avoid the synchronisation and run time issues while doing firmware updating and polling sensors values. Also, it is more specific to PMBus device and not talked about other devices firmware updates.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/54589\n\nThis design doc explains about enhancement/improvement in the current implementation of firmware update. It proposes the new Simple API's 'UpdateFirmware', 'SignaturePath' instead of itemUpdater/ImageManager interfaces and API's.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/55290\n\nThis design doc explains about shell based firmware update. This proposes, D-Bus APIs to provide firmware update and version reporting capabilities and simple firmware update API (UpdateFirmware and GetFirmwareUpdateStatus) and the Software.Version interface to command line utilities for firmware updates using a new daemon.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/55287\n\nThis design doc explains about Generic firmware update workflow. It proposes to implement the generic firmware update and flashing for all the device and flexible workflow for read/write and verifying the image. This design talks about update workflow will be split into three sections - Stage, Activate, Update.\n\n\nOur designs is specific to firmware update of multiple devices and custom flash tool. I think, this is align and relevant to with the last two design docs only \n\nneed to discuss on this with community and google team to merge into common framework."
                }
            ],
